 ■bãi cát (ở bờ sông, biển)

Anh - Anh
sandbank
■ noun a deposit of sand forming a shallow area in the sea or a river.

sentences.en: 91 of the Eurozone's top banks were part of the test, which, EU regulators say, was tougher than the U. S. bank stress test conducted last year.
